            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "First of all, I would like to thank the Narayana Vidhyashram School Founder Mr. Suresh sir for changing the adamant behavior and lifestyle of our beloved son S. Daiwik.\nWe expected the below changes in Daiwik while joining NVS (in June 2020).\n1.\tHe should listen or respond to the questions asked to him. Atleast for what is your name.\n2.\tHe should chew and swallow the food. (Wherever we go we used to carry/give him Idly and sambar, because he did not chew other food properly.)\n3.\tHe should stand for more than 10 seconds in one place. (He don’t know to walk, he will run always, he avoids eye contact.)\n4.\tHe can’t adapt to the new environment. (Even going to school, even potty training took 2 months).\n5.\tHe should hold parent hands while crossing the road or while we are in the new place.\n6.\tThe worst part is his addiction to gadgets.\nWe requested Suresh sir to help us to change Daiwik’s behavior in these activities.\nIn 1 year of time, we have seen below changes in Daiwik’s behavior,\n1.\tHe respond/listen to whomever asking the questions and paying attention to them. In addition to that he started asking lot of questions.\n2.\tHe started eating food properly: starting with vegetables, chicken lollypop, prawns are his favorite now. We are happy that no need to search for soft foods wherever we go.\n3.\tHe started asking what he want: water, toys, etc.\n4.\tHe is enjoying with new people now: relatives home, exploring new places and all.\n5.\tHis gadgets addition got reduced and he is enjoying playing with his toys, especially asking his dad to come play with him.\n6.\tWe can’t even give answer for some of his questions now.\n\nIf we go to other schools, they would have suggested to give some therapy to Daiwik, and it would be like hell. But NVS made everything possible.\nThe vegetables snack which NVS has suggested for breaktime is the starting where Daiwik started eating on his own!\nAnd then NVS has introduced Sprouts as snack in the morning breaktime. (I would like to appreciate the effort that NVS has taken in preparing the sprouts by themselves.) Even Doctors also prescribed us to add more proteins in the daily food for kids. Thanks for NVS for taking care of that part.\nSo, I personally request NVS to not stop giving sprouts to students. It’s a progressive thinking that NVS has taken, that should not be vain.",
